          <h2>What is Copenhagen Light Festival</h2>
          <p>
            The Copenhagen Light Festival is an annual event held in February,
            celebrating light art and illumination in Copenhagen. It showcases a
            variety of light-based works created by local and international
            artists, lighting designers, and students. The festival's curated
            program transforms the city's spaces, including squares, facades,
            bridges, and hidden places, into engaging, illuminated
            installations. Most of the artworks are located along a path in the
            inner city and harbor, with some outside the city center. This event
            invites people of all ages to experience the magic of light during
            the darkest and coldest time of the year in Copenhagen.
          </p>
        </article>
