          <h2>Vision and creative platform</h2>
          <p>
            The Copenhagen Light Festival should celebrate Nordic Lighting
            Design traditions by embracing unique Nordic daylight qualities.
            Prioritize both natural and artificial light quality, experimenting
            with colors, movement, and occasional sound to create immersive,
            meditative experiences. Balance between artificial and daylight is
            essential. The festival's goal is to showcase light as an expressive
            and transformative art form while connecting with local light
            appreciation.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Respect of and in balance with the darkness.</li>
            <li>
              Installations that improves life through interaction with human
              needs, architecture and spaces.
            </li>
            <li>
              Optimal balance between function, aesthetics and sustainability.
            </li>
            <li>
              Examples of minimalistic beauty and functionality to honour the
              Scandinavian Design traditions.
            </li>
            <li>
              Examples of festive and expressive installations, to the take
              advantage of a temporary element.
            </li>
